#week-title("One", "Philosophy of Putrefaction")

=== Core Teaching

Putrefaction is not death — it is the necessary stage by which a fixed thing is
returned to the volatile, so that it may be reconstituted at a higher level.

The *Golden Chain of Homer* devotes entire chapters to demonstrating that all three
kingdoms — animal, vegetable, and mineral — are born of the volatile and fixed
seeds and are returned to them through putrefaction. Decay is not the end of a
thing; it is its return to its source, from which new generation proceeds.

#doctrine[
  _"Minerals are born of fermented, putrefied salt and nitre turned acid. Even the
  most fixed mineral substance traces its origin to a putrefied, fermented
  water."_
  #align(right)[— _Golden Chain of Homer_, Part II]
]

=== Topics This Week

- Putrefaction as the return to the source
- The cycle of generation and corruption
- The necessity of dissolution for higher reconstitution

#inner-work[
  *The Lesson of the Grave*

  Contemplate the alchemical Nigredo as an extended putrefaction. Why must the
  outer form be destroyed for the inner essence to be released?

  Record your reflections on the relationship between "decay" and "potential" in
  your journal.
]

